On International Youth Day, the President celebrates the potential of young people to shape the future. With more than half of the global population under 30, young generations will find solutions to global challenges. The United States is committed to providing opportunities for young people to be leaders and change agents. This includes ensuring equal access to education, building skills in leadership, and supporting young entrepreneurs. Through initiatives like Young Leaders, nearly half a million young people are working together to effect change in their communities. Youth are often at the forefront of advocating for advancements in human rights, technology, climate change, and healthcare. The President commemorates the energetic spirit of young people worldwide and their ability to improve the future.